      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@Julian I think <i>must</i> is the right term because it is a rule, not a recommendation. If you use the annotation where you <i>should not</i> pass <code>null</code> but it would be allowed, you are using the annotation wrong. The term does not imply that it is validated. However, a hint that it is not validated wouldn&#39;t hurt. If you want to add automatic validation, you can use some external tools. For example, the <i>IntelliJ</i> IDE has builtin support to inject null-checks."
