    "question_id" : 34094039,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>As mentioned above <code>@NotNull</code> does nothing on its own. A good way of using <code>@NotNull</code> would be using it with <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Objects.html#requireNonNull(T,%20java.lang.String)\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>Objects.requireNonNull</code></a> </p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Foo {\n    private final Bar bar;\n\n    public Foo(@NotNull Bar bar) {\n        this.bar = Objects.requireNonNull(bar, \"bar must not be null\");\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4814165,
      "reputation" : 4307,
      "user_id" : 3886740,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 92,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d344e3015e4d001e7726260c4c76c937?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "sisanared",
